---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const frontmatter = {
  title: "Best Cabernet Sauvignon - Expert Guide",
  description: "Discover the best best cabernet sauvignon. Expert recommendations, tasting notes, and tips from certified sommeliers.",
  pubDate: "2026-01-14",
  author: "Elena Martinez",
  authorRole: "Senior Wine Writer",
  keywords: ["best cabernet sauvignon", "best", "cabernet", "sauvignon", "wine guide"]
};
---

<BaseLayout title={frontmatter.title} description={frontmatter.description}>
  <article class="container py-8 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <header class="mb-8">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-wine-800 mb-4">Best Cabernet Sauvignon</h1>
      <p class="text-gray-600">By Elena Martinez, Senior Wine Writer | Updated 2026-01-14</p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose prose-wine max-w-none">
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">When it comes to best cabernet sauvignon, quality matters more than price. Our team of sommeliers has tasted hundreds of options to bring you these expert recommendations.</p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-wine-700 mt-8 mb-4">Quick Answer</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700">The best options combine quality, value, and availability. We recommend exploring wines from established producers with consistent track records.</p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-wine-700 mt-8 mb-4">Our Top Picks</h2>
      
      <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-6 mb-4">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">1. 2019 Abeja Abeja Cabernet Sauvignon</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-2"><strong>Producer:</strong> Abeja</p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-2"><strong>Region:</strong> Columbia Valley, Washington</p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-2"><strong>Variety:</strong> Cabernet Sauvignon</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mt-3">Rich cassis and plum flavors with hints of graphite and spice.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-6 mb-4">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">2. 2019 Andrew Will Winery Andrew Will Sorella</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-2"><strong>Producer:</strong> Andrew Will Winery</p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-2"><strong>Region:</strong> Horse Heaven Hills, Washington</p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-2"><strong>Variety:</strong> Cabernet Sauvignon</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mt-3">Rich cassis and plum flavors with hints of graphite and spice.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-6 mb-4">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">3. 2019 Betz Family Winery Betz Family Winery Pere de Famille Cabernet Sauvignon</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-2"><strong>Producer:</strong> Betz Family Winery</p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-2"><strong>Region:</strong> Columbia Valley, Washington</p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-2"><strong>Variety:</strong> Cabernet Sauvignon</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mt-3">Bold and structured with blackcurrant, cedar, and tobacco notes.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-wine-700 mt-8 mb-4">Expert Tips</h2>
      
      <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-3 text-gray-700">
        <li><strong>Temperature matters</strong> - Serve whites chilled (45-50°F) and reds slightly below room temperature (60-65°F)</li>
        <li><strong>Decanting helps</strong> - Give bold reds 30-60 minutes to open up</li>
        <li><strong>Trust your palate</strong> - The best wine is the one you enjoy most</li>
        <li><strong>Consider the occasion</strong> - Match wine intensity to food intensity</li>
        <li><strong>Ask for help</strong> - Wine professionals love sharing their knowledge</li>
      </ol>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-wine-700 mt-8 mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">What should I look for in best cabernet sauvignon?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Focus on balance, quality producers, and wines that match your taste preferences. Price isn't always an indicator of quality.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">How much should I spend?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Great options exist at every price point. For everyday enjoyment, $15-30 offers excellent value. For special occasions, explore the $40-80 range.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">How do I store wine properly?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Keep bottles on their side in a cool, dark place (55°F ideal). Avoid temperature fluctuations and direct sunlight.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <hr class="my-8 border-gray-300" />
      <p class="text-gray-600 italic">Elena Martinez is a Senior Wine Writer with WSET Level 2 Award in Wines, Certified Specialist of Wine (CSW).</p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
